HEADWORD: Stylaster
<hw>Sty*las"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>sty^los</grk> pillar + <grk>'asth`r</grk> star.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of numerous species of delicate, usually
pink, calcareous hydroid corals of the genus
<gen>Stylaster</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

